The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for predicting students' grades in different courses, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of real-world data collected from a higher educational institute, which could be categorized under computer engineering (cs.CE) or information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of collaborative filtering and matrix factorization techniques also suggests a possible connection to database systems (cs.DB). Finally, the paper's focus on predicting student performance aligns with the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
